			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of 21-year-old I. Á. on the deportation of his family to Kamenets-Podolsk in 1941, the murder of his mother and siblings,
					his escape and return to Budapest, his labor service in the Hungarian Army, the deportation of his unit from Budapest to
					Sachsenhausen in December 1944, forced labor in Siemensstadt near Berlin, a death march at the end of the war to Hamburg, and his
					liberation by US troops in Schwerin.</p>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
