	<text>
		<body>
			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-DEGOB0748_01.jpg"/> The person in question has given us the following information: In <date when="1941"
					>1941</date>, I was taken into Poland <note type="gloss">The testimony is not precise. The survivor was taken to the occupied zone
					of the former Ukraine.</note> together with my father and six brothers, from where I managed to run away. When <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1034" type="subject">Hungary</term> was reunited with its historical parts
				I was in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName>, but I took days off to visit my parents
				home, and we were all <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deported</term> during these
				two weeks into Poland <note type="gloss">The testimony is not precise. The survivor was taken to the occupied zone of the former
					Ukraine.</note>. They crossed the borders with us and then let us free telling us to go wherever we wanted to. We crossed the
				Polish <note type="gloss">The testimony is not precise. The survivor was taken to the occupied zone of the former Ukraine.</note>
				border at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/688365/yasinya.html">Kőrösmező</placeName>, we could not turn back as they would
				have <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> us but could continue in the
				direction of the centre of the country. In Poland <note type="gloss">The testimony is not precise. The survivor was taken to the
					occupied zone of the former Ukraine.</note> we got into a forest where the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> and <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1124" type="subject">gendarmes</term> were shooting at us.
				Unfortunately, I saw how they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">shot</term> my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">mother</term> and my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">brothers</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">sisters</term>. I managed to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">run away</term> and walked fast till <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3081425/volovec.html">Volóc</placeName>, this is how I got back to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1034" type="subject">Hungary</term>. Not much later, I came to my firm in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Pest</placeName> but was summoned already at the end of <date
					when="1943">1943</date>(<date when="1941">41</date>) to do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-560"
					type="subject">labour service</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3050907/jaszbereny.html">Jászberény</placeName>
				where I passed five months before I was transferred into a company in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html"
					>Pest</placeName>. From the end of <date when="1942-12">December 1942</date> till the end of <date when="1944-12">December
					1944</date>, I was in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName> in an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-560" type="subject">anti-air raid company</term>, then I was put into an
				unfamiliar company. Having entrained 75 of us in a car at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html"
					>Józsefváros</placeName> railway station they carried to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-803"
					>Sachsenhausen</placeName>. During the journey sitting <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207"
					type="subject">people</term> kept swapping with standing ones as space was so little that we could not sit down all. We were
				escorted by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1124" type="subject">gendarmes</term> till the <term
					type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarian</term> border where they gave us to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>. In the car someone committed <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-217" type="subject">suicide</term>, and two weak <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> were trodden to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term>. At the <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_austrians">Austrian</term> border they opened the doors and we got <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">zulag</term>. There were 3,500 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> in our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> and the journey lasted ten days. The
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> was a collecting <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term>. In <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-803">Sachsenhausen</placeName> they disinfected us, seized what they could
				and dressed us in striped <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">clothes</term> and wooden
				shoes. In <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-803">Oranienburg</placeName> we were grouped according to
				professions, this is how I got to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin-Siemensstadt</placeName>, next
				to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2950159/berlin.html">Berlin</placeName>. Here they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selected</term> the strong and the weak. I was put
				into an outlying <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-489" type="subject">kommando</term>, we carried iron
				railway lines, railway sleepers, which was a very difficult job. For this <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> we had the worst possible <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food supply</term>. There was an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term> foreman who got there because of
				punishment. <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-DEGOB0748_02.jpg"/> He was the one who distributed the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> giving us only three quarters of a litre
				of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">soup</term> instead of a litre, and stole also
				from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> portions, so we became really
				weak, many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term>, and often we ate also <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potato peels</term>. These foremen and block leaders
				beat us with batons but we also suffered a lot of cold. One day I put a blanket under my <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">clothes</term> but was noticed by the foreman who
				reported it to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>. They gripped my hands
				and feet and gave me 100 blows, another time I got a slap so strong that the eardrum broke. A great number of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> because of cold, of maltreatment and of
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-570" type="subject">starvation</term>, especially young boys. They
				often <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1105" type="subject">bombed</term> the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005083">Siemens</orgName> company, at the end the whole <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> burnt down so they took me back to
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-803">Sachsenhausen</placeName>. I stayed here 8 days when we
				got an order to set off as the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Russians</orgName> were
				already pretty close. We had to queue up immediately and leave but as we were the last <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> there was no <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> left for us. We started our <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">march</term> on foot in the direction of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2911298/hamburg.html">Hamburg</placeName>, towards the sea, 40 kilometres a day. We were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">starving</term> so much that on the way we attacked
				locust trees and finished all their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">leafs</term> but
				we were not particularly choosy, we ate also <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
					>grass</term>. Once we noticed a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potato</term>
				clamp and started to run to it but the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
				shot at us and I got a bullet in the head. Those who were left behind on the road were covered with a blanket. This is how I passed
				half a day, then I got out and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">ran</term> across the
				woods towards <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2834282/schwerin.html">Schwerin</placeName>. 17 kilometres further <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">I met</term> the first <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_americans">American</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">soldier</term>. They put a bandage on my head and
				took me into a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">sanatorium</term>. This happened the
					<date when="1945-05-02">2nd of May</date>. Thereafter I had a good life, I got everything I wanted, and was carefully treated for
				a month. I went to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2875601/luebeck.html">Lübeck</placeName>, and applied for one of the <term
					type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs">Czech</term> transports. I came to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName> via <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName> and <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Pozsony</placeName>. My future plans: At the moment I work here in
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3054643/budapest.html">Budapest</placeName>, later I would like to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">emigrate</term> to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-906" type="subject">Palestine</term>.</p>
		</body>
